{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a689370-4f71-4ad1-b576-dbd4876cf7da","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it — **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform** when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`).\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Run tests with `dotnet test` as before, but the underlying runner changes.\n- CLI output format will differ slightly.\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not apply; check your runsettings file for compatibility.\n- If you use `dotnet test --filter`, the filter syntax remains the same.\n- Extensions like code coverage or loggers may need their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"20ca239f-1804-40e2-9791-c1aa2bc804b8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request in a specific repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":335},"id":"ed157777-ca51-4477-b2aa-e50c1529eb39","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:45:32.346Z","parentId":"e8a3e9a4-3822-4600-b1d9-15b2efda88a6"}
